This paper proposes a framework for generating a closed-loop walking engine for a humanoid robot, which involves the use of a dynamics model and a low-level controller. This topic is closely related to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as it involves developing algorithms for controlling the movements of a robot. The use of a Linear-Quadratic-Gaussian (LQG) controller also suggests that this paper may fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of optimization algorithms (such as genetic algorithms) to find the optimum parameters, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
